you know, then we-- our mind
getting more distracted.

00:24:53.860 --> 00:24:57.510
Then it becomes 47% or more.

00:24:57.510 --> 00:25:00.840
47% is average.

00:25:00.840 --> 00:25:04.760
And recent studies
at also UC-Davis

00:25:04.760 --> 00:25:11.510
have found that our
mind is primarily

00:25:11.510 --> 00:25:15.090
stuck in negative thinking.

00:25:15.090 --> 00:25:19.490
Our mind feels more comfortable
in negative thinking

00:25:19.490 --> 00:25:22.440
than positive thinking.

00:25:22.440 --> 00:25:25.470
So our mind is more deeply
rooted in negative thought

00:25:25.470 --> 00:25:29.560
patterns usually.

00:25:29.560 --> 00:25:32.700
So the UC-Davis studies
showed that-- th

00:25:32.700 --> 00:25:37.230
they did research with
the usually Group A,

00:25:37.230 --> 00:25:40.130
Group B, same amount of people.

00:25:40.130 --> 00:25:49.150
And then they had this
medical treatment as a thing

00:25:49.150 --> 00:25:50.490
to do the research here.

00:25:50.490 --> 00:25:54.130
And so they asked
Group A and told them

00:25:54.130 --> 00:26:02.200
that this medical treatment
has 70% of success.

00:26:02.200 --> 00:26:04.820
And so everybody had
positive thought about it.

00:26:04.820 --> 00:26:10.500
They all say if I have to
do it, in that situation,

00:26:10.500 --> 00:26:14.729
I would definitely
take this treatment.

00:26:14.729 --> 00:26:16.520
And then they went to
Group B and told them

00:26:16.520 --> 00:26:23.760
that this treatment has
30% chance of failure,

00:26:23.760 --> 00:26:25.380
like in the research,
how they do.

00:26:25.380 --> 00:26:29.420
And so that group thought-- they
had negative thought about it.

00:26:29.420 --> 00:26:32.220
And they thought
they really don't

00:26:32.220 --> 00:26:35.187
want to do it if they have to
do it, and so forth and so on.

00:26:35.187 --> 00:26:36.770
And then they went
back to the Group A

00:26:36.770 --> 00:26:41.870
and told them that not
only is 70% success rate,

00:26:41.870 --> 00:26:44.280
but does there's a
30% chance of failure.

00:26:46.890 --> 00:26:49.250
And then they changed
their mind right away

00:26:49.250 --> 00:26:52.960
from positive to negative.

00:26:52.960 --> 00:26:57.620
So most of them in Group A, they
had a negative thought about it

00:26:57.620 --> 00:27:01.490
now, even though their
first thought was positive.

00:27:01.490 --> 00:27:04.780
And then they went back to
the Group B and told them,

00:27:04.780 --> 00:27:13.490
it's not only 30% failure
rate, but also 70% success.

00:27:13.490 --> 00:27:15.020
But you know what?

00:27:15.020 --> 00:27:16.780
That didn't change their mind.

00:27:16.780 --> 00:27:18.770
They stayed negative.

00:27:18.770 --> 00:27:20.950
They stayed negative.

00:27:20.950 --> 00:27:24.150
And so the studies
showed that changing

00:27:24.150 --> 00:27:26.950
from positive to negative
is just an instant.

00:27:26.950 --> 00:27:29.480
And our mind is
habituated in that way.

00:27:29.480 --> 00:27:31.170
It flips right away.

00:27:31.170 --> 00:27:34.040
It doesn't take
that long to flip,

00:27:34.040 --> 00:27:36.560
but flipping from
negative to positive

00:27:36.560 --> 00:27:40.220
is extremely
difficult. That's what

00:27:40.220 --> 00:27:45.230
we call habit, repetitive
habit, habitual pattern here.

00:27:45.230 --> 00:27:49.300
And so the UC-Davis
studies show also

00:27:49.300 --> 00:27:57.390
that it takes three
positive thoughts to balance

00:27:57.390 --> 00:27:59.050
with the one negative thought.

00:27:59.050 --> 00:28:02.860
Just to balance-- we're not
talking about transforming

00:28:02.860 --> 00:28:04.240
or changing or anything.

00:28:04.240 --> 00:28:07.480
Even just a balance, you
need three positive thoughts

00:28:07.480 --> 00:28:10.980
for one negative thought.

00:28:10.980 --> 00:28:14.870
And so, therefore, if you
don't take care of our mind

00:28:14.870 --> 00:28:20.790
here, and direct
our mind positively,

00:28:20.790 --> 00:28:26.670
it is pretty clear that our
usual habit, in general,

00:28:26.670 --> 00:28:28.840
is to get stuck in
a negative space.

00:28:32.900 --> 00:28:35.800
And then that's where you don't
find any sense of happiness,

00:28:35.800 --> 00:28:38.670
joy, or achievement.

00:28:38.670 --> 00:28:48.100
So, therefore, the
reason why we get

00:28:48.100 --> 00:28:49.870
stuck in such a
negative thought pattern

00:28:49.870 --> 00:28:54.350
is because of our habitual mind.

00:28:54.350 --> 00:28:57.170
And what we are
habituated usually

00:28:57.170 --> 00:29:00.865
is we are habituated
in labeling process.

00:29:05.290 --> 00:29:08.530
Anything we experience,
we need to label.

00:29:08.530 --> 00:29:13.450
What we see, what we hear,
what we experience-- we always

00:29:13.450 --> 00:29:15.800
mix that with labels.

00:29:15.800 --> 00:29:19.940
And we mix that with
thought processes.

00:29:19.940 --> 00:29:23.150
And so when you mix them
with thought processes here,

00:29:23.150 --> 00:29:28.610
then you lose the original power
or the original experience.

00:29:28.610 --> 00:29:35.660
So what you're experiencing
