and calligraphy.

00:37:59.740 --> 00:38:02.142
And so, I mean, I love it.

00:38:02.142 --> 00:38:03.350
And there's a beauty to that.

00:38:03.350 --> 00:38:06.580
You can smell the bamboo.

00:38:06.580 --> 00:38:10.210
You're making a
pen, your own pen.

00:38:10.210 --> 00:38:14.740
I didn't quite learn how to make
paper, but they do teach that.

00:38:14.740 --> 00:38:18.490
And so, anyway, so remember
when you write calligraphy

00:38:18.490 --> 00:38:21.850
in that way, the more you
focus, the more you think,

00:38:21.850 --> 00:38:23.990
like, I shouldn't
make mistake, then

00:38:23.990 --> 00:38:27.240
that's when you make a mistake.

00:38:27.240 --> 00:38:30.040
That's when I make the mistake.

00:38:30.040 --> 00:38:38.820
And so the more we think we need
to be mindful, focus narrowly,

00:38:38.820 --> 00:38:43.250
squeeze your attention so
hard, when you try so hard,

00:38:43.250 --> 00:38:46.350
sometimes that has
counter-productive.

00:38:46.350 --> 00:38:51.650
And so mindfulness needs
some sense of relaxation,

00:38:51.650 --> 00:38:52.905
the balance of relaxation.

00:38:58.330 --> 00:39:03.380
In fact, some tradition
of meditation in the East,

00:39:03.380 --> 00:39:06.010
like from Tibetan
tradition, even

00:39:06.010 --> 00:39:11.990
say that one and only thing
you really need is relaxation.

00:39:11.990 --> 00:39:13.186
That's all you need.

00:39:13.186 --> 00:39:15.510
If you can relax, that's enough.

00:39:15.510 --> 00:39:20.355
But can you imagine
totally relaxing?

00:39:23.520 --> 00:39:27.450
Totally relaxing is
almost not possible.

00:39:27.450 --> 00:39:29.480
But when somebody tells
you to be mindful,

00:39:29.480 --> 00:39:33.250
you feel, like, no,
I can't be mindful.

00:39:33.250 --> 00:39:35.290
But when somebody
tells you to relax,

00:39:35.290 --> 00:39:36.780
then we feel like,
I can't relax.

00:39:36.780 --> 00:39:38.750
I have to focus.

00:39:38.750 --> 00:39:40.670
[INAUDIBLE] all this focus.

00:39:40.670 --> 00:39:45.360
And so you can see the shifts
between focusing and relaxing

00:39:45.360 --> 00:39:50.120
is already there in
your mind's make-up.

00:39:50.120 --> 00:39:53.020
It's nothing new you need
to find from outside.

00:39:53.020 --> 00:39:55.690
It's already there.

00:39:55.690 --> 00:39:56.940
Can you see?

00:39:56.940 --> 00:39:59.860
That when someone tells you
to one point of your focus,

00:39:59.860 --> 00:40:04.030
you feel like, I can't do that,
My mind kind of a spacious--

00:40:04.030 --> 00:40:06.490
goes into all this
kind of space.

00:40:06.490 --> 00:40:09.250
But then when somebody tells
you to completely relax

00:40:09.250 --> 00:40:12.650
and don't focus at all, then
we feel, I can't do that.

00:40:12.650 --> 00:40:16.390
My mind goes into
this-- mind goes

00:40:16.390 --> 00:40:21.360
to this object or flower or
person or whatnot, a thought.

00:40:21.360 --> 00:40:25.320
And so these two things
are already there

00:40:25.320 --> 00:40:26.730
as part of your mind's make-up.

00:40:29.550 --> 00:40:35.980
And so you need to balance
the two in terms of finding,

00:40:35.980 --> 00:40:43.200
in terms of discovering our
mind and the awareness that's

00:40:43.200 --> 00:40:44.810
looking at the mind.

00:40:44.810 --> 00:40:50.830
You need to balance between
mindfulness and relaxation,

00:40:50.830 --> 00:40:55.440
focus yet relaxed, relaxed
but not distracted.

00:40:58.280 --> 00:40:59.120
That's the key.

00:40:59.120 --> 00:41:03.660
And that's the hardest piece
here because just to do one

00:41:03.660 --> 00:41:04.970
is easy.

00:41:04.970 --> 00:41:09.020
But to have the balance is not.

00:41:09.020 --> 00:41:10.200
It's not that easy.

00:41:10.200 --> 00:41:12.970
And so working with
our emotions begins

00:41:12.970 --> 00:41:16.060
with working with a
sense of mindfulness.

00:41:16.060 --> 00:41:20.840
Mindful, we need
the sense of a gap.

00:41:20.840 --> 00:41:24.380
And when we have the gap
or the space between you

00:41:24.380 --> 00:41:28.120
and your emotions, then
you have an opportunity

00:41:28.120 --> 00:41:31.980
or a possibility of seeing
your emotions clearly.

00:41:31.980 --> 00:41:34.687
And once you can see
your emotions clearly,

00:41:34.687 --> 00:41:36.270
then you have a
possibility of letting

00:41:36.270 --> 00:41:42.945
go of that emotion
that's bothering you.

00:41:42.945 --> 00:41:46.440
There's no way we can
let go without seeing

00:41:46.440 --> 00:41:49.110
that emotions clearly.

00:41:49.110 --> 00:41:53.997
And so I want to read you this
last thing, letting go piece.

00:41:57.480 --> 00:41:58.442
I like this story.

00:42:01.100 --> 00:42:05.090
Is it OK I read this to you?

00:42:05.090 --> 00:42:07.470
A psychologist
walked around a room

00:42:07.470 --> 00:42:12.130
while teaching stress
management to an audience.

00:42:12.130 --> 00:42:16.460
As she raised a glass
of water, everyone

00:42:16.460 --> 00:42:22.140
expected Debbie asked the half
empty, half full question.

00:42:22.140 --> 00:42:24.690
Instead, with a
smile on her face,

00:42:24.690 --> 00:42:30.690
she inquired, how heavy
is the glass of water?

00:42:30.690 --> 00:42:35.460
Answers called out ranged
from eight ounce to 20 ounce.

00:42:35.460 --> 00:42:40.770
She replied, the absolute
weight doesn't matter.

00:42:40.770 --> 00:42:43.332
It depends on how
long I hold it.

00:42:46.230 --> 00:42:51.370
If I hold it for a minute,
it's not a problem.

00:42:51.370 --> 00:42:57.210
If I hold it for an hour,
I'll have an ache in my arm.

00:42:57.210 --> 00:43:04.010
If I hold it for a day, my arm
will feel numb and paralyzed.

00:43:04.010 --> 00:43:08.560
In each case, the weight of
the glass doesn't change,

00:43:08.560 --> 00:43:13.050
but the longer I hold it,
the heavier it becomes.

00:43:13.050 --> 00:43:15.300
She continued.

00:43:15.300 --> 00:43:17.980
The stresses and
warriors in life

00:43:17.980 --> 00:43:20.270
are like that glass of water.

00:43:20.270 --> 00:43:24.420
Think about them for a
while and nothing happens.

00:43:24.420 --> 00:43:30.110
Think about them a bit longer,
and they begin to hurt.

00:43:30.110 --> 00:43:34.300
And if you think about
them all day long,

00:43:34.300 --> 00:43:38.810
you'll feel paralyzed,
incapable of doing anything.

00:43:38.810 --> 00:43:42.120
It's important to remember
to let go of your stresses

00:43:42.120 --> 00:43:44.850
as early in the
evening as you can.

00:43:44.850 --> 00:43:46.590
Put all your burdens down.

00:43:46.590 --> 00:43:50.380
Don't carry them through the
evening and into the night.

00:43:50.380 --> 00:43:54.130
Remember to put the glass down.

00:43:54.130 --> 00:43:58.790
So I like this
analogy of letting go.

00:43:58.790 --> 00:44:02.510
The Buddhist meditation
teaching always

00:44:02.510 --> 00:44:09.170
says that we need to let go
of our clinging, our grasping,

00:44:09.170 --> 00:44:10.530
and holding on to things.

00:44:13.090 --> 00:44:18.050
And so the letting
go piece is really

00:44:18.050 --> 00:44:20.540
the hardest part
of our practice,

00:44:20.540 --> 00:44:25.870
I think, hardest thing to
do in our life, letting go.

00:44:25.870 --> 00:44:31.910
That's where you can see how
many junk we collect at home.

00:44:31.910 --> 00:44:34.050
Some of your empty
yogurt containers,

00:44:34.050 --> 00:44:36.580
we'll wash them and
keep them, think you

00:44:36.580 --> 00:44:40.340
we will use them for
flour or something.

00:44:40.340 --> 00:44:43.170
So we collect all kinds of junk.

00:44:43.170 --> 00:44:46.000
In the same way, we collect all
kinds of junk in our thought,

00:44:46.000 --> 00:44:48.600
in our mind that
we need to let go.

00:44:48.600 --> 00:44:53.450
Otherwise, we become
a mental hoarder.

00:44:53.450 --> 00:44:55.820
We're hoarding all kind
of negative thoughts,

00:44:55.820 --> 00:44:57.580
all kind of emotions.

00:44:57.580 --> 00:45:00.700
If we don't clean,
if we don't let go,

00:45:00.700 --> 00:45:03.635
then it becomes problematic.

00:45:03.635 --> 00:45:05.860
Like you need to clean the
search history from time

00:45:05.860 --> 00:45:07.670
to time.

00:45:07.670 --> 00:45:08.754
Or what do you call that?

00:45:08.754 --> 00:45:09.254
Cache?

00:45:13.970 --> 00:45:16.230
I mean, I'm not really
a computer person,

00:45:16.230 --> 00:45:22.352
but I'm one of the
persons that you

00:45:22.352 --> 00:45:31.890
are trying to make me use the
products that you develop.

00:45:31.890 --> 00:45:35.550
So I've been using a
lot of Google products.

00:45:35.550 --> 00:45:36.560
It's been pretty good.

00:45:41.580 --> 00:45:45.290
Is there a complaint
department somewhere?

00:45:45.290 --> 00:45:46.150
I'm just kidding.

00:45:46.150 --> 00:45:47.280
No, no complaints.

00:45:47.280 --> 00:45:49.170
It's good.

00:45:49.170 --> 00:45:50.669
Google Maps are excellent.

00:45:50.669 --> 00:45:52.460
And so I'd like to
thank you all very much.

00:45:52.460 --> 00:45:57.120
And especially I want to
thank our host here, Tom,

00:45:57.120 --> 00:45:58.670
for having me here.

00:45:58.670 --> 00:46:05.500
And I want to thank you,
Ming, for you excellent work

00:46:05.500 --> 00:46:09.010
with the search inside yourself
and all the program that

00:46:09.010 --> 00:46:13.330
continues here at
the Google campus.

00:46:13.330 --> 00:46:18.490
And so one last thing I want to
say is when you do meditation,

00:46:18.490 --> 00:46:24.510
if you are a meditator,
you're usually working

00:46:24.510 --> 00:46:26.730
with the breath, for example.

00:46:26.730 --> 00:46:29.810
Breathing in, breathing out,
you're focusing on the breath.

00:46:29.810 --> 00:46:32.370
You're trying to
concentrate your mind there.

00:46:32.370 --> 00:46:34.300
You're trying to
relax your mind there

00:46:34.300 --> 00:46:37.840
through breathing, through
one point of focus,

00:46:37.840 --> 00:46:39.750
through relaxation.

00:46:39.750 --> 00:46:44.640
And then from time to
time, look at the looker

00:46:44.640 --> 00:46:48.910
inwardly, not always looking
at the breath or any kind

00:46:48.910 --> 00:46:53.290
of meditative techniques you use
from all kind of world wisdom

00:46:53.290 --> 00:46:54.590
tradition.

00:46:54.590 --> 00:46:59.890
But sometimes you look at
the observing mind itself,

00:46:59.890 --> 00:47:01.760
observer.

00:47:01.760 --> 00:47:05.830
And sometimes when you have
emotions, don't just label it.

00:47:05.830 --> 00:47:08.830
Don't just look at the
object of your emotions,

00:47:08.830 --> 00:47:11.760
but look at the energy,
the experience of emotion

00:47:11.760 --> 00:47:18.390
that you feel inside of your
heart and see the energy,

00:47:18.390 --> 00:47:24.582
connect with the energy,
and pause right there.

00:47:24.582 --> 00:47:32.800
One of the biggest problems
we see in our American culture

00:47:32.800 --> 00:47:35.975
is that all of us try
to express everything.

00:47:38.800 --> 00:47:39.520
That is good.

00:47:39.520 --> 00:47:40.380
Expressing is good.

00:47:40.380 --> 00:47:41.670
It's nothing bad.

00:47:41.670 --> 00:47:44.165
But expressing can take
place a little bit later.

00:47:48.450 --> 00:47:53.350
Just take a few moments
before you express.

00:47:53.350 --> 00:47:57.875
That can save you a lot
of trouble and money.

00:48:00.930 --> 00:48:02.700
Sometimes you express
too early, and that

00:48:02.700 --> 00:48:03.960
causes so much therapy.

00:48:03.960 --> 00:48:06.620
And that's expensive.

00:48:06.620 --> 00:48:11.510
So I think it's important
for us to take a minute

00:48:11.510 --> 00:48:15.050
and look at our own
experience of emotions

00:48:15.050 --> 00:48:21.070
before we try to share or
experience that with anyone.

00:48:21.070 --> 00:48:23.340
Positively or negatively,
it doesn't matter.

00:48:23.340 --> 00:48:25.390
Just take a moment to feel it.

00:48:25.390 --> 00:48:27.550
Good emotions, feel
it for a moment.

00:48:27.550 --> 00:48:30.040
Bad emotions, feel
it for a moment.

00:48:30.040 --> 00:48:31.790
And then you have
plenty of time to share.

00:48:31.790 --> 00:48:32.638
Thank you.

00:48:32.638 --> 00:48:34.510
[APPLAUSE]

